The introduction of the euro was a
bad idea, 60 percent of Germans said in a poll published today
by  Focus magazine .  The poll, carried out by TNS Emnid for Focus, found that 74
percent of Germans agreed that the deutschmark was more stable
than other currencies when compared with the euro, and that 85
percent said prices had increased significantly since the euroâ€™s
